President Xi Jinping on February 25 said his country has achieved “complete victory” over poverty following a series of programmes that lifted nearly 100 million rural folk from below the poverty line. China’s declaration of poverty eradication last week is being seen as a statement of intent on how it will deal with Africa and other regions in the near future, some analysts say.. 

President Xi Jinping on February 25 said his country has achieved “complete victory” over poverty following a series of programmes that lifted nearly 100 million rural folk from below the poverty line. 



