China plans to hold another FOCAC summit later this year in Senegal, with debate raging on whether it has indebted the continent. 

Its more than $150 billion in infrastructure loans have been scrutinised for opaqueness even as Beijing argues it has helped erect more than 1,000 crucial projects on the continent since 2010. 

